                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.1012 Anti-War/76: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 25, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Your No. 70, April 24, 6 p.m. You may agree to substitution of “Senate” for
                    “Government” in clause you quoted. President’s full power authorizing you to
                    adhere in name of United States to Anti-War Treaty issued April 24 and will be
                    forwarded by mail.</p>
                <p>I shall be glad to have you make appropriate remarks on the occasion of adhering.
                    Hull</p>
            </div>
        </body>
